originalText.text:
After working with them for 3 years on a multi-million dollar social strategy for an international non-profit, I've just re-hired them for a personal project. I went through a multi-round pitch process with their competitors last time. This time I'm saving myself the headache and just going with the best team.

For me, two factors sealed the deal:
AAA-level creative talent
happy work environment

Let me elaborate. When I select an agency, I look for happy team members. If their employees are happy, if the vibe is strong, if they hang out together, that says to me there will be a low turnover. I've worked with agencies where I had three different account execs in a single year. That doesn't happen here. They run a tight ship but they have fun. I credit this to their hands-on leadership and the high value they place on creativity. It's harder to find than you'd think. I'd stake my reputation on recommending them. You can't go wrong.

originalText.text:
Finding an agency that treats your business like their own is difficult. In fact, until SocialQ we'd never felt like we were receiving the support we needed to take our digital efforts to the next level.

SocialQ is the third agency we've partnered with and they're by far the best. When working with them it feels like working with an internal team and like we're their only client. They're creative, hands-on, diligent, flexible, and organized - and honestly a joy to work with. And best of all, they get results.

I highly recommend!
